{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Rxq9qG5hqLPxhePHhdvFAy","type":"tool_result","content":"# Askewly Design System Index\n\n## Entry Protocol\n**URL:** https://ui.askewly.com/llms/docs/design-system/entry-protocol.md\n\n**Summary:** The entry protocol serves as the starting point for design work. It provides a task-specific workflow guiding users on \"what to fetch, in what order\" based on whether they're creating a new screen, refining existing UI, or working on an individual component.\n\n## Core Documentation Entries\n\n**Principles & Guidance:**\n- Design principles emphasizing task-first hierarchy, semantic tokens, complete interaction states, meaningful motion, and evidence-based decisions\n- Anti-pattern checklist with 12 clusters covering cost integrity, destructive actions, and accessible interaction paths\n- Style signature document with 5 operating principles and 5 hard-fail dislikes (including left-border accent cards and emoji icons)\n\n**Design Tokens & Variables:**\n- 3-tier token system (primitive/semantic/component) in DTCG 2025.10 format\n- Ready-to-use CSS custom properties for light and dark modes\n\n**Taxonomy & Contracts:**\n- 7 surfaces, 10 pattern groups, 57 classified groups\n- Recipe format specifications and component restyle contracts\n- Expressive stack tier mapping for rendering techniques (CSS/SVG through WebGL)\n\n**Recipe Categories:** 40+ draft recipes spanning application UI, commerce, data display, documentation, feedback, forms, layout, marketing, navigation, and overlays."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5a57d822-e398-4198-9dc4-ceadd30199eb","uuid":"fee6b5ed-9fe4-4967-993a-b8fbb04cb3cd","timestamp":"2026-07-18T14:51:12.022Z","tool_use_result":{"bytes":12617,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Askewly Design System Index\n\n## Entry Protocol\n**URL:** https://ui.askewly.com/llms/docs/design-system/entry-protocol.md\n\n**Summary:** The entry protocol serves as the starting point for design work. It provides a task-specific workflow guiding users on \"what to fetch, in what order\" based on whether they're creating a new screen, refining existing UI, or working on an individual component.\n\n## Core Documentation Entries\n\n**Principles & Guidance:**\n- Design principles emphasizing task-first hierarchy, semantic tokens, complete interaction states, meaningful motion, and evidence-based decisions\n- Anti-pattern checklist with 12 clusters covering cost integrity, destructive actions, and accessible interaction paths\n- Style signature document with 5 operating principles and 5 hard-fail dislikes (including left-border accent cards and emoji icons)\n\n**Design Tokens & Variables:**\n- 3-tier token system (primitive/semantic/component) in DTCG 2025.10 format\n- Ready-to-use CSS custom properties for light and dark modes\n\n**Taxonomy & Contracts:**\n- 7 surfaces, 10 pattern groups, 57 classified groups\n- Recipe format specifications and component restyle contracts\n- Expressive stack tier mapping for rendering techniques (CSS/SVG through WebGL)\n\n**Recipe Categories:** 40+ draft recipes spanning application UI, commerce, data display, documentation, feedback, forms, layout, marketing, navigation, and overlays.","durationMs":6607,"url":"https://ui.askewly.com/llms.txt"}}
