{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SXNBv9DydziuV8Z5AqDiKD","type":"tool_result","content":"# Task: Adding hover style to existing save button\n\nBased on the protocol, this is a **small component fix** that skips the full design brief interview.\n\n## Exact steps:\n\n1. **Skip the brief interview.** The protocol states: *\"a small component fix skips it.\"* You already have an existing page with established styling, so no DESIGN.md interview is needed.\n\n2. **Identify your token source.** Check if `page.html` or its project has existing design tokens or a `DESIGN.md` file. If yes, derive the hover state from those tokens only. If no, then fetch [`tokens/tokens.css`](https://ui.askewly.com/llms/tokens/tokens.css) as a fallback.\n\n3. **Consult anti-patterns.** Fetch [`docs/design-system/anti-patterns.md`](https://ui.askewly.com/llms/docs/design-system/anti-patterns.md) to identify failure modes specific to button hover states (e.g., insufficient contrast, unclear affordance, inconsistent timing).\n\n4. **Implement the hover state** using semantic tokens, ensuring you cover the full interaction spec: hover, focus, active, and disabled variants if they don't already exist.\n\n5. **Self-judge before reporting.** Fetch [`docs/design-system/style-signature.md`](https://ui.askewly.com/llms/docs/design-system/style-signature.md) and verify all 5 operating principles apply to your button refinement. Include this judgment in your report.\n\n6. **Verify the result** — check WCAG contrast passes, dark mode holds, and capture a screenshot.\n\n7. **Wait for human confirmation** before considering the work complete."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5a57d822-e398-4198-9dc4-ceadd30199eb","uuid":"800f46a1-918c-4db2-bce0-e0ccb263f6a4","timestamp":"2026-07-18T14:51:21.719Z","tool_use_result":{"bytes":6190,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Task: Adding hover style to existing save button\n\nBased on the protocol, this is a **small component fix** that skips the full design brief interview.\n\n## Exact steps:\n\n1. **Skip the brief interview.** The protocol states: *\"a small component fix skips it.\"* You already have an existing page with established styling, so no DESIGN.md interview is needed.\n\n2. **Identify your token source.** Check if `page.html` or its project has existing design tokens or a `DESIGN.md` file. If yes, derive the hover state from those tokens only. If no, then fetch [`tokens/tokens.css`](https://ui.askewly.com/llms/tokens/tokens.css) as a fallback.\n\n3. **Consult anti-patterns.** Fetch [`docs/design-system/anti-patterns.md`](https://ui.askewly.com/llms/docs/design-system/anti-patterns.md) to identify failure modes specific to button hover states (e.g., insufficient contrast, unclear affordance, inconsistent timing).\n\n4. **Implement the hover state** using semantic tokens, ensuring you cover the full interaction spec: hover, focus, active, and disabled variants if they don't already exist.\n\n5. **Self-judge before reporting.** Fetch [`docs/design-system/style-signature.md`](https://ui.askewly.com/llms/docs/design-system/style-signature.md) and verify all 5 operating principles apply to your button refinement. Include this judgment in your report.\n\n6. **Verify the result** — check WCAG contrast passes, dark mode holds, and capture a screenshot.\n\n7. **Wait for human confirmation** before considering the work complete.","durationMs":5931,"url":"https://ui.askewly.com/llms/docs/design-system/entry-protocol.md"}}
