{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UdSJokinQBR89T8uViBQkm","type":"tool_result","content":"# Button Hover States: Anti-Pattern Summary\n\nThe document doesn't contain a dedicated cluster on button hover states, contrast, affordance, transition timing, or cursor behavior.\n\nHowever, **Cluster 7 (Token System Bypass)** addresses button styling broadly: \"Do not hardcode visual effects like 'heavy drop shadow, gradient fill' outside the design token system.\" This indirectly applies to hover states—avoid inventing custom shadow or color transitions that bypass `tokens/askewly.tokens.json`.\n\n**Cluster 14 (Pure Ink/Paper)** notes that AI outputs default to \"high-contrast, harsh-looking\" base values. This principle would extend to hover states: avoid pure `#000`/`#fff` contrast shifts; use calibrated tints/alpha adjustments instead.\n\nThe guide focuses on broader UX failures (accessibility, state clarity, data honesty) rather than micro-interactions. For button hover specifics, you'd need to check the referenced recipe `recipes/forms/button.md` directly, which the document cites for anti-patterns but doesn't excerpt in detail."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5a57d822-e398-4198-9dc4-ceadd30199eb","uuid":"84afa40a-0220-4ac0-94d2-d5173579d1a4","timestamp":"2026-07-18T14:51:50.992Z","tool_use_result":{"bytes":21544,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Button Hover States: Anti-Pattern Summary\n\nThe document doesn't contain a dedicated cluster on button hover states, contrast, affordance, transition timing, or cursor behavior.\n\nHowever, **Cluster 7 (Token System Bypass)** addresses button styling broadly: \"Do not hardcode visual effects like 'heavy drop shadow, gradient fill' outside the design token system.\" This indirectly applies to hover states—avoid inventing custom shadow or color transitions that bypass `tokens/askewly.tokens.json`.\n\n**Cluster 14 (Pure Ink/Paper)** notes that AI outputs default to \"high-contrast, harsh-looking\" base values. This principle would extend to hover states: avoid pure `#000`/`#fff` contrast shifts; use calibrated tints/alpha adjustments instead.\n\nThe guide focuses on broader UX failures (accessibility, state clarity, data honesty) rather than micro-interactions. For button hover specifics, you'd need to check the referenced recipe `recipes/forms/button.md` directly, which the document cites for anti-patterns but doesn't excerpt in detail.","durationMs":4605,"url":"https://ui.askewly.com/llms/docs/design-system/anti-patterns.md"}}
